reviews.name: Zimmer
reviews.text: LIke many others have stated, the "Out of Beans" light constantly comes on even with a full coffee hopper. When this occurs, it dumps the puck and flushes the machine - NO coffee. The experts at "Whole Latte Love" say, "no problem, just run 20 shots though it on the lowest settings" this will RECALIBRATE the grinder" Why would a BRAND NEW machine need to be recalibrated??? Other suggested solutions include disassembling the brand new machine and re-build the grinder! WTH??
reviews.title: More maintenance than espresso. Does NOT WORK out of box.

reviews.name: Carlo Cappello
reviews.text: Having owned superautomatica coffee machines in the past, I’m disappointed with the amount of coffee beans this machine wastes. I’m constantly having stir the coffee beans in the hopper so they’re processed by the grinder properly. Even when I manually agitate the coffee beans in the hopper, the machine will show the “out of beans” code in the display when the hopper is full. Something clearly isn’t working properly. Disappointing.
reviews.title: Wastes too much coffee

reviews.name: Thao
reviews.text: It is very easy to make drip coffee. You just add the water, beans, and pick your size of cup. It basically creates an Americano with an espresso like puck of coffee. The coffee has a little crema on the top which is nicer than almost all drip coffee machines that I have used but it isn't a real crema like you would have from an espresso machine Americano. You get options from 3 oz to 24 oz plus cooler brew
reviews.title: Great product

reviews.name: Bradley A Grigor
reviews.text: Our De'Longhi TrueBrew coffee maker replaces an old Mr. Coffee drip coffee maker and separate Capresso grinder. It was not that these were bad machines--they worked OK. However, my wife thought the coffee tasted dull.
reviews.title: Awesome coffee, many options, love it!!

reviews.name: Nonie VINE VOICE
reviews.text: I am picky about my coffee and have owned many brands of coffee maker. I was hesitant to buy this because I've never spent this much on a machine before but my husband encouraged me to get it for my birthday. I read all the reviews and watched the videos and was persuaded by the many that raved about the coffee flavor. They were all right! It is the best I've had and I love it. The features make it versatile coffee in size
reviews.title: This Spoiled Me for Other Coffee Makers

reviews.name: queenbee shopper
reviews.text: After much reading (good and bad) I did decide to purchase this item. While it is quite pricey, it does have some great features. You'll fill the machine with beans and water, which will last several days depending on your use. Others have mentioned that it leaks, it's messy, etc. I clean my machine every day. When I say clean, that really means emptying the excess water container and dumping the coffee grounds, then a quick wipe
reviews.title: Pricey but nice

reviews.name: PSeven
reviews.text: One drawback worth mentioning is the relatively small containers for flushed water and used coffee grounds. I find myself having to clear them every 4-5 times of use, which can be a bit inconvenient. Moreover, as some other reviews have noted, there are occasional leaks when emptying these containers, resulting in a messy clean-up process. While it's manageable, it would be great if these containers were more spacious and leak-proof.
reviews.title: Great Coffee machine with some Flaws, but deal-able

reviews.name: kelly kuster
reviews.text: I received my coffee maker for mothers day, and I absolutely love it. My husband and kids got it for me, I had never looked into getting this maker just because of it being on the pricey side. I'm so glad they got it, because it's perfect. I like the individual cup settings. We all like different sizes and boldness, it's perfect
reviews.title: I didn't know I needed this.

reviews.name: PoppyField VINE VOICE
reviews.text:
The TrueBrew is an awesome fully automatic coffee powerhouse for coffee lovers.
What we loved:
1. It uses whole beans and automatically grinds them for you! I loved this feature! Automatic grinders can be quite expensive and manual grinders can be hard to get the right coarseness, with this it was perfect every time. 2. It has a substantial water reservoir that does not need frequent refills. 3. You can set a timer to wake up to a fresh batch of coffee.
reviews.title: Ditch the pods for whole bean coffee with TrueBrew

reviews.name: workingstiff
reviews.text: My wife was diagnosed with MAR (melanoma associated retinopathy) and in the past eight months has lost 60% of her central vision. She is legally blind, can't drive, can't read books, can barely work on her computer. The one thing that she can do is still read a recipe, as long as it is in type size 48, but getting the proper measurements for her cooking and baking was virtually impossible.
reviews.title: Legally blind but can still cok and bake
